{"_id":"bc9e14559378291f","name":"A Whip as Sharp as a Blade","type":"object","img":"icons/weapons/whips/whip-barbed-metal.webp","system":{"description":"An exotic weapon wielded by Trebizond, the princess Paladin from a distant country. This special whip is as deadly as any blade, capable of slicing through flesh and armor with equal ease. As part of her 'From a Far Country' Gift, Trebizond can make use of weapons and exotic objects seized from foreign lands to surprise opponents. Once per scene, she creates a special belonging like this razor-sharp whip. When using her special equipment, Trebizond increases her Opposition Level by 1, demonstrating her mastery of unconventional combat techniques.","quantity":1,"weight":2,"value":300,"equipped":false,"properties":["Exotic weapon","Sharp as blade","Reach weapon","Enhances wielder","Paladin equipment","Single use per scene"]},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"b4840181e01953cb","name":"Fervor Tokens","type":"clue","img":"icons/sundries/gaming/token-shield-gold-red.webp","system":{"description":"Sacred tokens representing Saint George's holy zeal and righteous fury when facing monstrous enemies. The Holy Dragon Slayer starts each scenario with 1 Fervor Token and gains additional tokens whenever he suffers a wound. These tokens can be spent to grant allied Hunters additional wounds against visible monsters or provide defensive bonuses. When Saint George becomes an Opponent Dark Presence during a Witch Hunt, he gains Fervor Tokens equal to the number of Hunters, which he can use to inflict additional wounds or transform Hunter Position Checks into automatic failures.","location":"Tracked by Saint George during combat","importance":"important","found":true,"scenario":"saint-george-the-dragon-slayer"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"29940e772665d6de","name":"Judgment Tokens","type":"clue","img":"icons/sundries/gaming/token-balance-scale-gold.webp","system":{"description":"Tokens representing Saint George's recognition of the Hunters' good deeds and righteous actions despite their connection to the Broken Tales. When Saint George becomes an Opponent Dark Presence during a Witch Hunt, he can still accumulate Judgment Tokens if Hunters activate their Dark Ego to perform good deeds or use magical Gifts to help ordinary people in his presence. These tokens carry over between scenarios. When Judgment Tokens equal the number of Hunters, Saint George makes amends, declaring he was wrong in his judgment, and puts an end to the Witch Hunt - potentially restoring his role as an Ally Dark Presence.","location":"Tracked during Witch Hunt scenarios","importance":"crucial","found":true,"scenario":"saint-george-the-dragon-slayer"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"c2f1056e272f0ada","name":"Saint George's Holy Authority","type":"clue","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-sealed-brown-red-yellow.webp","system":{"description":"Official documentation and papal authority carried by Saint George, representing his position as the highest representative of the Papacy and his full authority over all members of the Order. This authority allows Saint George to command Hunters, judge their actions, and even initiate Witch Hunts against those he deems corrupted by the Broken Tales. The Holy Authority is both a symbol of the Church's power and a constant reminder to Hunters that they are being watched and evaluated by one of the Church's most skilled and zealous warriors.","location":"Carried by Saint George at all times","importance":"important","found":true,"scenario":"saint-george-the-dragon-slayer"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"e01ad3915ffb3fdd","name":"Suspicion Tokens","type":"clue","img":"icons/sundries/gaming/token-eye-black-red.webp","system":{"description":"Markers of Saint George's growing distrust and suspicion toward the Hunters he accompanies. The Judgment of the Saint Gift tracks these tokens whenever a Hunter activates their Dark Ego, uses magical Gifts, or terrorizes ordinary people in Saint George's presence. During scenes, the Storyteller can spend Suspicion Tokens to impose penalties on Hunter Checks. These tokens carry over between scenarios, building toward a breaking point. When Suspicion Tokens equal twice the number of Hunters, Saint George initiates a Witch Hunt and becomes an Opponent Dark Presence, turning against the very Hunters he once supported.","location":"Tracked by the Storyteller throughout the campaign","importance":"crucial","found":true,"scenario":"saint-george-the-dragon-slayer"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"8851192ac100af88","name":"Trebizond's Magic-Finding Dust","type":"object","img":"icons/consumables/potions/potion-bottle-corked-labeled-blue.webp","system":{"description":"Exotic dust seized from a far country by Trebizond, the princess Paladin who serves Saint George. This special belonging allows Trebizond to detect and track magical presences. As part of her 'From a Far Country' Gift, once per scene she can create special equipment like this Magic-Finding Dust or A Whip as Sharp as a Blade. When using her special equipment, Trebizond increases her Opposition Level by 1, making her particularly dangerous to Hunters who rely on magical abilities.","quantity":1,"weight":0.5,"value":200,"equipped":false,"properties":["Magical detection","Exotic","Single use per scene","Enhances wielder","Paladin equipment"]},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
